						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up near the ruined temple of Subrahmaṇya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1725, Duṁdubhi, Māgha, śu. 2, Monday.</p>						

						<p>Records the erection of Swinging-pillars in the temple of Kōmavalli by Kōṭa-Sachiva of Prattipāḍu.</p>						

